Date: Fri, 29 Oct 93 01:02:44 +0100
From: Eberhard_Moenkeberg@p27.rollo.central.de (Eberhard Moenkeberg)
Subject: Re: Way Low Bogomips


Hello Mark and all others,

on 27.10.93 Mark Gray wrote to All in USENET.COMP.OS.LINUX.MISC:

>>>>>>>>>>> 486DX-33 -----> 16.5 bogomips
>>>>>>>> 486DX66/2 --> 34.06 BogoMips (tm)
>>>>>> 486DX50/2  ---> 25.0 BogoMips (tm)
>>>>> 486SX25  ---> 12.24 BogoMips (tm)
>> 486DX40 ---> 19.97 BogoMips (tm)

MG> I can't see worrying about some 10% difference, but:
MG> 486DX-33 --->  4.66 BogoMips
MG>
MG> It is only 1.45 BogoMips with internal and external (256k) cache off.
MG> AMI setup says the speed is "high"

My AMI sometimes wants to tell me I had a DX2 CPU (it is a 486DX40)...

MG>  and turbo button is disabled (good since I don't have one).

Nice description... If I switch "turbo off", the 19.97 BogoMips (tm)
melt down to 4.41 BogoMips (tm).

So, if you do not have a turbo button, put a "turbo jumper" onto the
turbo switch connector pins on your motherboard.

Greetings ... Eberhard


