>...
>But how do you explain 2 diff. BogoMips on the exact same machine? One is
>from SLS1.03 (33.55) and the other from Slackware 1.04 (33.22). Do they use
>diff? algorithms or so?
>
I'm quite sure there'd be more than one explanation - but how about those
two kernels placing the BogoMips code at two different locations, and these
different locations happening to fall into two different (1MB) chips?

But there is another one - all else being equal, do you always get the same
BogoMips rating when you boot your system 10, 20, 30 times? ALWAYS?


